But I am charmed by artful expression and eloquent prose. I edit a newsletter, and write in my free time. In college I had my fair share of public speaking experiences. The basics about me - I worked till recently for the strategy consulting major Booz Allen Hamilton based out of Chicago. I am currently a senior manager with Wal-Mart in its corporate strategy group. Before leaving for the US for business school, I worked for six years with India's leading automotive manufacturer at Delhi and Kolkata. I am cheerful, vibrant; I love life and laughter - a definite optimist. Classmates described me as: Very genuine, intelligent- intellectually and emotionally, honest and considerate about others, has a strong sense of values and is willing to stand up for what he believes in, creative, willing to sacrifice for others, exudes decency, strives to build relationships. Ok, all this sounds extraordinarily pompous, so I will let it be. :-) But seriously, I am under no illusion of being picture perfect (pun intended). And I would be equally happy to acquaint you with my negatives. The only reason I wrote out the above is to highlight what I would love to see in you. More importantly, I am looking for someone who truly respects herself. Someone who is confident, knows her own mind and yet secure enough to remain kind. I would love it if you radiate a healthy, positive attitude - are someone ready to share a silly joke and a hearty laugh. Like they say - dissimilarities attract, but similarity is the glue that keeps couples together through the rough and tumble of life. I do take out time to pursue my passions and have fun! My interests comprise doing pro bono social work, public speaking, reading, cooking, yoga, writing, understanding people and cultures, and a variety of sports. I am enthusiastic about learning dance, and have been regular at the gym for a while now. Oh, and I haven't answered the geography question for myself yet. The right person will have a huge say on whether its back to India or the US for me. Looking ahead, life seems to hold so much on offer and there is so much more to learn. I am fascinated already by the journey ahead. A path that can become more fulfilling and fun with a soul mate. Would love to hear if you have similar thoughts. ========= I grew up in a very warm and loving family. As an Army officer's kid, I guess I was exposed to a variety of places, people and experiences during my childhood. My father has since retired as a Brigadier, and is based at Noida near Delhi. I have two elder brothers who are officers in the Indian Army and Navy respectively.,,,28 to 34,21 Jul 1974,,United States of America,,Slim,,,Rajput,,,,Fair,,Self,MBA/PGDM,"39 yrs, 5ft 8in,

column1: I am a survivor. I have been through a lot, but haven't lost my child like innocence. I feel its my biggest strength. I respect all viewpoints but like to live as my unique self. I am easy to talk to. I love having conversations and being able to apply what I learn as I go along. I am attached to my home and love making it mine by working in it. I am equally comfortable in solitude and company.I believe in evolving and growing in a relationship.I believe in choosing what adds value to me and what I can sustain in the long run. I love the outdoors and pursue sports and athletic activities as a conscious lifestyle choice. I love relaxing with a movie or a book or just eating out.I am a reasonably moderate spender and believe in quality and value as the deciders in making purchasing decisions as much as cost and budget. I am well read and spiritual. I like to listen to all viewpoints but prefer to let my own mind and judgement make my decisions for me.I believe having a relationship, a vocation and a personal calling are the three pillars of the modern man or woman's existence, and each reinforce and strengthen the other in equal measure.I believe in staying positive, cheerful and "on the move", regardless of changes and circumstances, using one's personal passion as the foundation on which to live one's life. I believe thinking big and having a large heart is essential to me.That said,it is little things done daily that make me feel cared for and loved.I love the idea of falling for someone in love and believe it is worth everything you go through in it. I also feel being raised in a loving and stable family has imbued me with a deep sense of integration and compassion towards my fellow human beings. I believe in being a lifelong student of life. I love the feeling of being timelessly invested in the feeling of love. I do believe there are ups and downs and do not fear them. I find myself quite grounded and at peace with myself. It would be lovely to know people more than I have had to.,"She must be sincere, caring and true to herself. She must appreciate the efforts needed to make it in the long haul. column1:
Hey, I m Indrajit hear.Managing Director.SLIEVERS AGRI BIOTECH. I do some travelling first. Planning on spending this December in America ..so you can make your own conclusion :)
I am passionate about learning, about sharing new ideas, about traveling to new places, about being an independent and empowered man, but I also long to meet a loving companion, to build a family and to share my destiny. I want to love and be loved, to touch and be touched, and to move beyond myself, to share a wonderful life with the right woman. The most important quality should be intelligence. I want to know someone who will be my full partner in living and learning. Yet intelligence must come with compassion and a loving heart. She is also an outdoorswoman who is hooked on pop culture and isn't afraid to cry during sappy movies. For me integrity, self discipline, and diligence are the keys to a healthy life. Life is a journey, it is not a destination. Life is neither easy nor fair. One must be strong minded. I enjoy everyday life, and take responsibility for everything I do. A person must be ready to compromise when seeking a happy marriage. It requires that one take a risk. I have reached the point in my life when I want to take that risk. I am at an independent, attractive, well educated Man. I am ready to meet and engage the right Woman. I am out going and approachable, but I am also reserved and traditional. Are you ready for this? Let journey begin,"
About My Partner

She should be a friend easy to talk to about anything and everything. Should be able to take on responsibilities , a matured individual , with a focused thought process .Negative Egostist attitude is a complete NO . Should be fun loving, would be able to accept me with my positive waves and negative waves. Career , ambitions , professionalism should not overshadow family , togetherness , warmth and peace of mind.

I know nobody is perfect , neither am I , nor I want a perfect Woman , I wish to share and live , enjoy each others company for the rest of my life with a lot of positive warmth , love , and peace of mind.",,,06 Aug 1974,01:02:00,India,Aizwal,Average,Average,,Brahmin - Bengali,Bengali,,,Very Fair ,Very Fair,Self,MBA/PGDM,"39 yrs, 5ft 7in,

column1: The fragrance of rain drenching the parched earth, the flash of lightning against an ink-blue sky, the temple bells chiming on festival day... itA?s these small pleasures in life that make me happy. For me, festivals related to Lord Krishna are very important A he is our family deity after all. But I respect all religions and faiths. When I am passing by a church, gurudwara or masjid, my hands immediately fold into a Namaste as a mark of reverence. For me all religions are the same and lead to almighty. ItA?s just that each one professes it in a different way. My soul mate should respect my sentiments. For a relationship to be successful, it must be based on mutual understanding. Just as I donA?t expect my partner to blindly follow my faith, he too should give me the space to follow mine.,"Person whom i am looking for should be affectionate, understanding, caring and be honest. column1:
About Me 
"...Hi, this is Vinay Mehta from Bombay, a Punjabi Hindu boy, convent educated & presently working with Universal Music Group as Manager AA?A? Finance & Accounts for the last 7 years with a annual package of 5.5 Lacs. I am C.A Finalist. Hobbies - listening music, gardening, reading, somewhat athlete. In Search of a good looking, with good values, good natured, educated & a decent partner, working or non AA?A? working is immaterial, also caste no bar. I would like my partner to give some time to my house & should know cooking. I am ready to take care of her financially & physically, would like to keep her happy throughout. For me marriage is understanding, respecting, trusting, adjusting with patience & for taking it forward successfully, each day requires a lot of maturedness. For me wife in not a servant, also husband is not. I personally clean up my house with vaccum on a monthly basis & do a lot of outdoor shopping for kitchen. I am strictly a non-smoker & non alcoholic, but very rarely I eat non veg. No non-veg items are cooked in our house. I am slim with decent looks & tall. I have a lovely house with a personal garden. I am not interested in dowry or in making any kind of a demand, but in exchange would like to have a nice partner.AA?A? "...Something more about myself. I am a divorcee. I have worked overseas in Oman, Qatar & Hong Kong earlier, but now settled with this company in Bombay. Since I work for a music company I love to listen to music while working and have good music stuffAA?A?s of all kind. I need a partner with whom I can share my thoughts, day to day activities, enjoy my rest of my life & would love to keep her smiling and happy all the time. 

About My Family
Father is a retired qualified engineer. Mother is a graduate homemaker. We are fully settled in Bombay, Borivali, from the last 35 years & having ownership house in society building at ground floor with a personal garden. Native place is Delhi. Ours is a very small family & believe in straight forwardness. Parents are not dependent on the son. Financially we are sound.  Not a single paise demand will be made ( i.e No Dowry ),"About The Partner

I would like to have a partner who is educated, friendly, social, with ethics &  cultural values, good looking, honest, beautiful &  homely. Full co-operation will be provided to her from my side &  from my parents to make her settle. Caste is No Bar. I would prefer to take a partner with a issue preferably a small girl child  &  I would be legally giving her my name, needless to mention the  affection &  love would be there for the child throughout. I have a beautiful daughter aged somewhere 4 yrs but after the breakup the entire rights &  custody now has been given to my ex-wife. I have no contacts with them. The daughter has not stayed with me since birth for a single day. But yes I miss my daughter at times. We can assure with supporting legal documents that the ex-wife &  daughter will not come in our life.
Thanks for reading &  those seriously interested in settling in Bombay please contact me or my parents without hesitation....""

column1: It is a daunting task to sum up oneself (or anybody, for that matter) in a boxed space! The basics about me - I am currently in India having just graduated from a top-tier business school in the US. I am working for the strategy consulting major Booz Allen Hamilton in Chicago. Before leaving for the US,I worked for Maruti Udyog in Dealer Development, Market Strategy and Sales (1996-02, Delhi and Kolkata). I am an optimist, a cheerful and vibrant guy - and I love to laugh. I strive to live life to its fullest. During one of my business school courses, classmates described me as: Very genuine, intelligent- intellectually and emotionally, honest but also very considerate about others, has a strong sense of values and is willing to stand up for what he believes in, extremely creative, unselfish, willing to sacrifice for others, flexible and able to accommodate other viewpoints, extremely well-mannered, exudes decency, strives to build relationships and understand others. At this point, I think this list sounds seriously pompous, so I will let it be. :-) The only reason I wrote out the above list of qualities is to highlight what I would also love to see in my partner. She must be somebody who respects herself. Someone who is confident, yet kind and compassionate. Someone who radiates a healthy, positive attitude and a delicious sense of humour. While dissimilarities attract, research says the similarity between couples is the glue that keeps them together through the rough and tumble of life. My interests comprise doing pro bono social work, public speaking, reading, cooking, yoga, writing, understanding people and cultures, and a variety of sports. I have been regular at the gym for a while now. I am on a mission to learn golf during this vacation (ok, that was overstating it :-) - but I am going to take a shot at learning the basics). I grew up in a very warm and loving family. As an Army officer's kid, I guess I was exposed to a variety of places, people and experiences during my childhood. My father has since retired as a Brigadier. I have two elder brothers who are officers in the Indian Army and Navy respectively. I believe it important to keep growing as a person throughout life. I carry a spiritual understanding of human life and of the world we live in. A couple genuinely in love would feel free to truly discover and be their own selves in their marriage. At this point in life, if I look back I feel I have travelled quite a distance. But looking ahead, I realize life has so much more to offer and there is so much more to learn. I am sure a fascinating journey lies ahead. It is a journey that each of us can make infinitely richer and more fulfilling with a soul mate and life partner. I would love to hear from you if you have similar thoughts.,Check my profile for details on this.,,29 to 34,21 Jul 1974,,India,,Slim,Slim,,Kshatriya,,,,Wheatish ,Doesn't Matter,Self,MBA/PGDM,"39 yrs, 5ft 8in,

column1: I am a highly educated, talented, ambitious, open-minded, affectionate, sensitive, simple and well cultured person. Looking for my soul-mate who is also having the same qualities from the Lingayat community or from any other caste....... Being an artist, musician, poet and a writer I taught in some of the well known and prestigious colleges for 8-9 years. Now I have been teaching Indian classical music. As a person of ideals, I hate and oppose the evils of our social system like casteism, dowry, etc..... Marriage, as I feel, should not just be a relation, but the meeting of two intellects, rationale, talents and pure hearts... As I am having such qualities in me, naturally and necessarily I expect all these qualities from the girl who is going to be my soul-mate; I expect all these because, I do not like the woman just as a domestic worker and a pleasure partner of somebody, as she has been considered and treated throughout our history and present. I expect my would-be wife to be of that height of my level by means of intellect, talent, knowledge, pure heart, and virtue. I strongly believe and hold this view, and I say these only are the true riches we as parents can pass on to our children and future generation through our genes. I expect the girl (preferably working in govt. or private) who meets all these qualities. .... I live an intellectual life, who consider the life without a higher & noble goal to achieve and intellectualism is just waste.... by this, please don't think that, I am under estimating or disrespecting the common people, for whom actually I have a lot of respect which they deserve naturally. What I am trying to emphasize or convince is the animals which are born in the form of HUMAN should live, behave, act and THINK like HUMAN... and must be HUMANE! People in this state know me very well as a progressive thinker and writer. Thousands of students study my writings as the text as a part of their syllabus in colleges, and many esteemed magazines and publications have published many of my articles. I expect a girl with such qualities and abilities, who is really INTELLECTUAL, TALENTED, and HUMANE & KIND HEARTED, who will be a venerable goddess and rule my heart...!!!,"I expect my would be wife to be of that hight of my level by means of intellect, talent, knowledge, pure heart, and virtue. I strongly believe and hold this view, and I say these only are the true riches we as parents can pass on to our children and future generation through our genes. I expect the girl (preferably working in govt. or private) who meets all these qualities can contact me.",,24 to 40,20 Aug 1974,01:40:00,India,Gulbarga,Average,Doesn't Matter,,Lingayath,Lingayath,,,Whetish Medium ,Doesn't Matter,Self,MA (Arts),"39 yrs, 5ft,

PERSONALITY:

Soft-spoken, humourous, ambitious, and spiritual oriented. 

Have a few close friends who are well versed, suave, and intellectual like. Popular with all the people for the gentle manner and enthusiasm. 

Interested in Psychology, Philosophy, History, Sociology, and Tamil literature. 

Enjoys nature, solitude, reading, and hybernating :-) !!

Loves a quite noiseless environment and a relaxed orderly life-style. 

Prefers to live an orderly life personally and expects it from near and dear (but doesn't force it). 

Loves to keep the body fit. 

PROFESSIONAL:

Working as a Lead Technical Writer in Ness Technologies, Bangalore. 

(Technical Writing is a profession popular in IT industries. The Technical Writer writes Manuals, Reference Guides, etc. for the software products. The profession is also known as Information Development. )

Have been frequently awarded by the present company as an excellent performer. There are credits from the earlier companies as well. 

Loves success than anything else. 

ASTROLOGICAL INFORMATION:

Makara Rasi; Uthrada nakshathra; Second Patham. 

EDUCATION:

Have done Masters in Information Science. 

And still learning a lot from people, profession and life. 

HOBBY:

Reading, Writing, and Discussing to learn, relax, and relish life. 

GROOM'S FAMILY:  
 
Groom's family Hail from Paeikkulam, Sri Vaikuntam, Tirunelveli. 

Grandfather Late Sri. Ramaswamy Iyer was an erstwhile landlord of high value in Tirunelveli. Father Late Sri. Vaikuntam had retired from bank and has been enjoying his life in Vaikuntalokam (or, is it Shivalogam?) for the past 5 years. Mother's name is Jayalakshmi. 

Groom was born in Madurai and brought up in Nilakottai. Education is in and around Madurai. 

Groom is the eldest son of the family. One sister happily married and with two kids; two brothers - elder is in search of a job after finishing his M. Sc. , IT and Multimedia course. Youngest has finished his Diplamo in Catering Technology and in pursuit of higher education.,"Partner Expectations:

Simplicity helps in avoiding the complexities and problems of life.  
I describe myself as a simple and decent person who is flexible and easily adjusting in any situation of life. Further, I like to spend most of my time listening to music, reading books, travelling to new places and watching movies.   
In my professional life I am working as a Cashier with Sudarshan Silks. I am a dedicated worker. Due to my dedication I have received a lot of  appreciation. I want to see myself growing and reaching a reputed position in life. 
My mother is a homemaker and father is a retired Custom Officer. I have a sister who is currently married and a brother who is running a business of his own.  
My school life was pretty smooth and I was a good student. After completing my school education I completed B Com from Bangalore University.
Friends play a major role in my life. I have few friends in my life who are very close to my heart. I can share my feelings and emotions with them only.,"I want my life partner to be simple and well qualified with a positive attitude towards life. She should come from a good family background, having a decent image in the society. Further, I would prefer a girl from Delhi/NCR region.

She will have the freedom to choose whether she would like to work or stay at home. It will be completely her decision to choose her profession. I would appreciate if she works as it will help her create her own identity and confidence.

I would prefer a girl from Karnataka who is well settled in her life. One of the important features I want in my wife is that she should not only respect me but my family also. This way she will gain a lot of respect and love in my eyes.
If she is the way I am looking for then she will get a lot of love from me.

Beaches, Music & Driving soothe me. A self made individual, I have my own style. Its easy to mistake pride vs arrogance. I am proud to have achieved whatever I have till now in my career and personal life and am also ambitious enough to pursue further. When I say "ambitious enough" I mean that for me a thorough work - life balance is very important. 
I am kinda offbeat when I say that weekends see me doing my household chores but that does not stop me from catching up with friends, movies, a long drive or just hanging and chilling out.
Passionate conversations over coffee with my partner, add a little twist of romance & humor, double it up with a good dinner n dance, is something I have been wanting and see myself happy with. Having few friends who I can vouch for I want someone who understands those bonds and treasures them the way I do.
Experiences have helped me evolve into a hearty disposition with a great deal of self assurance and confidence. At the same time it has taught me how important individuality and space is.
There is a lot more to write but I believe its the best when you hear it face to face rather than depend on glorified writings at times......more when we meet.,"I am looking for a partner who can challenge my thirst for adventure, surprise me with spontaneity, has an individuality of her own when it comes to her career (if working) and way of doing things. Someone who will help me balance my life even better. Space is something I highly respect and expect the same from my better half; and it goes both ways.

Love is the best when it is both ways. Having said that, I think every person is different, a lot of the other things can be worked upon. If we click together it is all the more worthwhile to change or tweak ourselves a bit for each other.

I have been waiting for my gurl for such a long time, I hope that she comes soon else I may have to dissappear in the wilderness :-)",,29 to 33,01 Jan 1974,09:10:00,India,Mumbai,Athletic,Athletic,,Others,,,,Fair ,Fair,Self,Masters,"39 yrs, 5ft 8in,

column1:
I am a single, never married, soft-spoken person who is polite with everyone and is very respectful of the views of others. I have been brought up with a mix of Indian traditions and modern liberal values. I am also a person with a very positive attitude and a lot of enthusiasm & zest for life. I always sees the glass "Half-Full" and not "Half-Empty". 

I believe strongly in sharing all the responsibilities with my future bride equally and will also give her the space and support she needs to develop her potential fully. 

I am a fair, slim, tall and handsome person according to my parents and friends. I speak Dutch and English fluently  and understand Tamil reasonably well. I also understand & speak German reasonably well.

I have completed my education in Accounting and am employed for several years as an Accounting and Administration professional. I am now pursuing the Dutch MBA qualification (Modern Business Accounting) through evening classes and  expect to complete these studies in 2008. 

My interests are listening to music, cycling, travelling to different countries, attending get-togethers, visiting relatives & historical places in India and watching selected movies & TV programs. I enjoy visiting India for holidays.

Some info about Holland: 

It is possible to take up further studies in Holland in the English language in various disciplines. 

Career opportunities in Holland are very good for Engineers (all branches), IT professionals, Accountants, Finance, Marketing and Customer Service Professionals. 

Career opportunities are also very good for Teachers in International Schools in which the medium of instruction is English. 

Holland is one of the most advanced and internationally oriented countries in Europe. London and Paris can be reached from Amsterdam (capital of Holland) in one hour by a flight. 

Most Indians living in Holland visit India every year to spend time with their relatives. 

Moreover, telephone costs are quite low now-a-days; so one calls one's relatives/friends in India quite often. In addition, one can also make PC to PC and PC to Land-line phone calls worldwide which cost almost nothing. 

There are about 100 Indian families living within 30 kilometres from our house. Hence one can have a good social life with Indians, besides the local Dutch people. 

The working hours in Holland are regulated by law and thus no one works beyond 8 AM to 6 PM for long periods. Only exceptionally, do people work in week-ends as well. Commuting times in Holland are also generally short like 30 minutes or less. Thus, balancing the domestic responsibilities with a professional career is a lot easier in Holland than in India and U. S. A. As a consequence, the overall quality of life is a lot better in Holland than in many western countries.

Moreover, there are a lot of part-time jobs available in Holland in all professions. This also helps to balance the career with domestic responsibilities more easily.

Will provide additional details about Holland if you have interest to proceed further.,"I am looking forward to meet a communicative, affectionate, understanding, moderately extrovert person who is brought up with a mix of Indian traditions and modern liberal values and who prefers inter-dependence with her life-partner rather than total independence on all matters.

My partner's hobbies and interests need not be identical to mine; however, I look forward to someone with whom I can share many things with interest and enthusiasm from both of us and get thru the journey of life having plenty of fun-filled moments.

Though English is widely spoken in Holland, girls who would enjoy learning a European language (Dutch) after coming to Holland, besides having an active professional career would be most suitable. Those who know German or French can easily learn Dutch. Obviously, I will enjoy helping my future bride to learn the Dutch language.
My future bride can decide herself whether she wants to continue with her career or be a home-maker.

My bride can also visit India to meet her relatives once a year on an average, excluding special occasions like weddings of close relatives/friends for which of course she can make an additional trip if required.

,Arvind emigrated to Holland (Netherlands) with his parents and one brother 26 years back. His only brother, also an Accounting professional, moved to Dublin, Ireland in Nov. 2003. Father: Electronics Engineer, retired from a MNC in Holland in a Senior Executive position. Mother: Graduate & Homemaker. The family is settled in Holland; however, all 4 persons have visited Mumbai/Chennai/Bangalore regularly.

We are a nuclear family and respect and follow Indian customs and traditions and both our sons are not ""overly westernised"". At the same time we are not orthodox. We believe we have the right balance between traditional and modern liberal values. Our sons respect elders and are proud of their Indian heritage.",25 to 30,13 Dec 1973,12:45:00,India,Others,Slim,Average,,Iyer,Brahmin,,,Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,B.Com (Commerce),"39 yrs, 5ft 9in,

column1: ,,"Presently, we are a nuke family of four my parents and my younger bro.
Our forefathers had routes in Punjab area of now a days Pakistan. Not hailed from an affluent financial background though needs are easily satisfied,
My Father owned a Shop of milk and dairy products since last 40 odd years .My Brother is running his work of DJ and catering in the city. Mom is a very pious home maker.
Presently we are staying in our ancestral house with my parents.It is 55 yard small typical two story buid onto free parental land situated in congested old area of the city.

Well build and neatly maintained. But our house is situated in a dense populated and Muslim surrounded area and that area not neat & clean and entrance is also not proper. I won't like to stay here but every time my planning to purchase or build my own house with a bank loan got crashed by one reason or another. I requested him to do a write-up about himself and this is what he came up with. Hi, I am an Electrical Engineer with Masters in HR & Marketing.
